<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c230_125"> 
<div id="v230.125.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4609 s"> of degrees</span><span class="H982 s">. They that trust</span><span class="H3068 s"> in the LORD</span><span class="H2022 s"> <i>shall be</i> as mount</span><span class="H6726 s"> Zion</span><span class="H4131 s">, <i>which</i> cannot be removed</span><span class="H3427 s">, <i>but</i> abideth</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.125.2"><span class="H2022 s">As the mountains</span><span class="H5439 s"> <i>are</i> round about</span><span class="H3389 s"> Jerusalem</span><span class="H3068 s">, so the LORD</span><span class="H5439 s"> <i>is</i> round about</span><span class="H5971 s"> his people</span><span class="H5704 s"> from henceforth even for</span><span class="H5769 s"> ever</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.125.3"><span class="H7626 s">For the rod</span><span class="H7562 s"> of the wicked</span><span class="H5117 s"> shall not rest</span><span class="H1486 s"> upon the lot</span><span class="H6662 s"> of the righteous</span><span class="H4616 s">; lest</span><span class="H6662 s"> the righteous</span><span class="H7971 s"> put forth</span><span class="H3027 s"> their hands</span><span class="H5766 s"> unto iniquity</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the wicked: Heb. wickedness)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.125.4"><span class="H2895 s">Do good</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H2896 s">, unto <i>those that be</i> good</span><span class="H3477 s">, and <i>to them that are</i> upright</span><span class="H3826 s"> in their hearts</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.125.5"><span class="H5186 s">As for such as turn aside</span><span class="H6128 s"> unto their crooked ways</span><span class="H3068 s">, the LORD</span><span class="H3212 s"> shall lead them forth</span><span class="H6466 s"> with the workers</span><span class="H205 s"> of iniquity</span><span class="H7965 s">: <i>but</i> peace</span><span class="H3478 s"> <i>shall be</i> upon Israel</span>.</div></div>

